  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Ag Photo Period Lighting Controller\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Ag Photo Period Lighting Controller\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Controls photoperiod and light intensity for indoor growing zones. Monitors PAR (photosynthetically active radiation) intensity, accumulated daily light integral (DLI), and dark-period integrity. Fires LIGHTS_ON/OFF transitions and DLI insufficiency alerts. Upstream: light sensors at [12:16]. Downstream: AgNutrientCycleOptimizer and AgIPMPestAlertMonitor read output at [32:36].\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- par_intensity_norm (index 0):  0.0 = dark | 0.5 = 400 \u00b5mol/m\u00b2/s (vegetative optimal) | 1.0 = 1000 \u00b5mol/m\u00b2/s\n- photoperiod_elapsed_norm (index 1):  0.0 = start of light period | 0.5 = mid-period | 1.0 = full period complete\n- dli_accumulated_norm (index 2):  0.0 = 0 mol/m\u00b2/d | 0.5 = 20 mol/m\u00b2/d (vegetative target) | 1.0 = 40+ mol/m\u00b2/d\n- dark_period_integrity_norm (index 3):  0.0 = dark period fully satisfied | 0.5 = partial dark | 1.0 = no dark period (light leak)\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- LIGHTS_ON (GREEN) -> action: Downstream IPM and nutrient cycle monitors register active photoperiod\n- LIGHTS_OFF (GREEN) -> action: Power down grow lights; dark period timer starts\n- PHOTO_OK (GREEN) -> action: Downstream nutrient and IPM monitors register healthy light environment",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "par_intensity_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "dark",
          "mid": "400 \u00b5mol/m\u00b2/s (vegetative optimal)",
          "high": "1000 \u00b5mol/m\u00b2/s"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "photoperiod_elapsed_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "start of light period",
          "mid": "mid-period",
          "high": "full period complete"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "dli_accumulated_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "0 mol/m\u00b2/d",
          "mid": "20 mol/m\u00b2/d (vegetative target)",
          "high": "40+ mol/m\u00b2/d"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "dark_period_integrity_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "dark period fully satisfied",
          "mid": "partial dark",
          "high": "no dark period (light leak)"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "ag-photo-lights-on-cycle",
        "label": "LIGHTS_ON",
        "rag": "GREEN",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Downstream IPM and nutrient cycle monitors register active photoperiod"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "ag-photo-lights-off-cycle",
        "label": "LIGHTS_OFF",
        "rag": "GREEN",
        "outputIndex": 1,
        "action": "Power down grow lights; dark period timer starts"
      },
      {
        "sequenceId": "ag-photo-ok",
        "label": "PHOTO_OK",
        "rag": "GREEN",
        "outputIndex": 3,
        "action": "Downstream nutrient and IPM monitors register healthy light environment"
      }
    ]
  },
